OL,3,CThe Welsh dad who lost his son at 27
OL,4,Cand now helps bereaved families
OL,6,FJesse said: "This is nice that the
OL,7,FWelsh Government has acknowledged the
OL,8,Fhard work the board of trustees, the
OL,9,Fcounsellors, everybody has put in.
OL,11,F"It's nice that we can drive this out
OL,12,Facross the whole of Wales so that the
OL,13,Fhelp can be there. But people have to
OL,14,Ftake up that help.
OL,16,F"They've got to think 'what if (the
OL,17,Fworst) happens?' and then it turns
OL,18,Finto reality. Then it's too late."
