OL,3,CThe Welsh dad who lost his son at 27
OL,4,Cand now helps bereaved families
OL,6,FThe support is available to
OL,7,Findividuals and families and can be
OL,8,Fprovided via phone, in person or by
OL,9,Fvideo call and is free and
OL,10,Fconfidential.
OL,12,FThe Welsh Government's Mental Health
OL,13,Fand Early Years Minister Sarah Murphy
OL,14,Fvisited the Jac Lewis Foundation's
OL,15,Fservice in Swansea.
OL,17,FShe said: "Bereavement after suicide
OL,18,Fcan be devastating and it is vital
OL,19,Feveryone affected can access
OL,20,Fcompassionate support in their time of
OL,21,Fneed.
